subSubSection.paragraph:
Etymology : Eύρωστoς (
evrostos
) means ‘robust’ in Greek, in reference to the great mediolateral thickness of the proximal extent of the scapula and massive build of the deltoid ridge.

Type horizon : Upper lower Maastrichtian strata of the Conques Formation, Tremp Group, eastern Tremp Syncline, northeastern Spain (
Fondevilla et al . 2016
) ( Fig. 1 ).

